<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HR00476</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : RESOLUTION URGING THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES THRU THE COMMITTEE ON COMMUNICATIONS JOINTLY WITH THE COMMITTEE ON WAYS AND MEANS AND COMMITTEE ON METRO MANILA DEVELOPMENT TO CONDUCT AN INQUIRY IN AID OF LEGISLATION INTO THE ALARMING STATE, UNDER PAR, AND SLOTH-PACED COMMUNICATION AND INTERNET SERVICE QUALITY, PROVIDED BY NETWORK OPERATORS. MISLEADING OFFERS HIGHLIGHT EVERY ADVERTISEMENT OFFER BY THESE TELECOMMUNICATIONS COMPANY. OVER SUBSCRIPTION AND BANDWIDTH ABUSE PRIMARILY CONTRIBUTE TO THE WORSENING INTERNET QUALITY TO THE GREAT PREJUDICE OF THE PUBLIC. WORST, THESE ACTS HAVE BEEN TOLERATED, UNDER SUSPICIOUS CIRCUMSTANCES, BY THE NATIONAL TELECOMMUNICATIONS COMMISSION (NTC), THE AGENCY TASKED TO REGULATE THESE ENTITIES. FURTHERMORE, THE UNCONTROLLED DISTRIBUTION OF UNREGISTERED PREPAID NUMBERS HAVE PAVED THE WAY FOR THE PROLIFERATION OF CRIMES, TERRORIST ACTIVITIES, AIDING AND ABETTING DRUG OF OPERATIONS TO GROW TO ASTRONOMICAL PROPORTIONS</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>TEVES, ARNOLFO JR. A., LOPEZ, MANUEL LUIS T., PINEDA, ENRICO A., ACHARON, PEDRO JR. B., SARMIENTO, EDGAR MARY S.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2016-10-13</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON INFORMATION AND COMMUNICATIONS TECHNOLOGY ON 2016-11-14</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PREVIOUS COMMITTEE REFERRALS :PRIMARILY REFERRED TO RULES on 2016-10-19;</td></tr></table>